info.name: [Shipping] Buy Shipping Flow
info.description: ## ðŸ“¦ What is Merchant Fulfillment Network? Merchant Fulfilled Network (MFN), also known as [Fulfillment by Merchant (FBM)](https://sell.amazon.com/programs/fulfilled-by-merchant), allows sellers to handle end-to-end fulfillment, using either their own logistics or third-party carriers. After listing products on Amazonâ€™s global marketplaces, sellers manage shipping when a customer places an order. To enhance efficiency, sellers can leverage Shipping Settings Automation (SSA) for accurate delivery estimates, Shipping Templates to configure rates, and Buy Shipping to access Amazonâ€™s negotiated carrier rates. By integrating MFN with Amazon's APIs, sellers can streamline fulfillment, ensure timely deliveries, and protect their seller performance metrics with automated tracking and dispute protection. > ðŸŽ¥ Find more information on FBM [here](https://youtu.be/_lzmMQVysRQ?si=c5viZKc8AXxD6ROz). ## ðŸšš What is Amazon Buy Shipping? [Buy Shipping](https://sell.amazon.com/tools/buy-shipping) is our built-in shipping label purchase platform where you can buy a shipping service from Amazon partnered carriers at the lowest available cost. Buy Shipping allows you to buy shipping labels individually or in bulk, ship and confirm your orders, and track your shipments. Using Buy Shipping helps safeguard your account from: 1. **Competitive rates:** Buy Shipping offers Amazon negotiated rates to sellers offering competitive pricing when compared to public rates. 2. **On time delivery:** Buy Shipping only suggests shipping services that can meet the delivery promise to the customer. 3. **Simplified booking process:** No need to visit the carrierâ€™s website for logistics booking. Select orders to be shipped and book shipments from the same Seller Central workflow. 4. **Fully tracked solution:** Automatic shipping confirmation for orders without having to manually re-enter the tracking ID, while ensuring 100% compliance with Valid Tracking Rate. 5. **A-to-z guarantee claims:** If you purchase Amazonâ€™s Buy Shipping and ship on time, you are protected against claims where a customer reports problems with delivery. Amazon will cover the cost of these claims and they will not affect your order defect rate. 6. **Negative customer feedback:** If you ship on time with tracking via Buy Shipping and the customer leaves seller feedback only on delayed or undelivered packages, you can request to have the feedback reviewed. To start using Buy Shipping, you have to open accounts with any of our integrated carrier partners and get the account linked to your Seller Central account. > ðŸŽ¥ Find more information on Buy Shipping [here](https://youtu.be/gHN4V2K38ZA?si=wSb5hhGc187NbdbC). ## ðŸ”‘ Key APIs in the Merchant Fulfillment Flow A well-architected Amazon Merchant Fulfillment workflow relies on several key APIs - [Orders API](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference) â€“ Retrieves order details, including customer information, payment status, and fulfillment preferences, forming the foundation of your fulfillment process. - [Notifications API](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/notifications-api-v1-reference) â€“ Enables real-time event tracking, such as order confirmations, shipping updates, and inventory changes, ensuring timely and automated responses. - [Shipping API v2](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/amazon-shipping/docs/shipping-api-v2-reference) â€“ Provides access to Amazonâ€™s shipping services, allowing you to compare rates, purchase labels, and track shipments efficiently. ## ðŸ’¡ Business Insights Buy Shipping service offers sellers a powerful solution to enhance their merchant-fulfilled operations with FBA-like efficiency. Sellers using this tool experience significant advantages: up to 31% reduction in shipping costs, 20% fewer potential late deliveries, and an average 31% better delivery promises. This comprehensive shipping solution helps sellers optimize their delivery performance while managing costs effectively, ultimately leading to improved buyer satisfaction and increased business growth. This Postman collection demonstrates the Buy Shipping workflow using the **Orders API and the Shipping API v2,** enabling sellers to purchase shipping for both **Prime** and **non-Prime** orders through Amazonâ€™s Buy Shipping services. ### ðŸ”¨ Key Features - **Subscribe to Order Notifications**: Automate order tracking with `ORDER_CHANGE` notifications via the **Notifications API**. - **Retrieve Order Details**: Identify and fetch orders from Amazon using the **Orders API**. - **Get Shipping Offers**: Use `getRates` to preview available shipping services based on order details. - **Get Additional Inputs:** This step is only needed for rates that return that they need extra inputs. Mainly for international shipments. - **Purchase Shipments**: Select a shipping service and confirm the shipment using `purchaseShipment`, automatically deducting the cost from the sellerâ€™s account. - **Print Shipping Labels**: Extract and print shipping labels in supported formats (PDF, PNG, or ZPL). - **Cancel Shipments**: Use `cancelShipment` to void a shipment when necessary. - **Get Tracking Information**: Use the `getTracking` functionality to stay updated with the latest shipment status. ## ðŸŒŠ Buy Shipping Postman Flow This collection includes a fully visualized **Buy Shipping** flow using Postman Flows. It showcases each step as building blocks, guiding you from input to a successfully generated shipping label. ### ðŸ› ï¸ What Youâ€™ll Need To test the flow, provide the following inputs: - `order_id`: A valid **Amazon Order Number** - **Package Details**: Weight and dimensions - **Label Dimensions** By default, the flow selects the **cheapest available shipping rate**, but you can customize this behavior directly in the flow logic. > ðŸŽ¯ This is a great way to explore a **well-architected Buy Shipping flow**, understand how each API block fits together, and see the full journey from order to shipping label. ## ðŸš€ How to Test This Flow ### âœ… Prerequisites #### 1\. Set **Environment Variables** Go to the **Environment Variables** tab and enter the following: - `client_id`: Your SP-API Appâ€™s **Client ID** - `client_secret`: Your SP-API Appâ€™s **Client Secret** - `refresh_token`: A valid **SP-API Refresh Token** - `marketplace`: The **Marketplace ID** you're operating in #### 2\. Set **Collection Variables** In the **Collection Variables** tab, provide: - `order_id`: A valid **Amazon Order Number** - `shipping_preference`: Choose one from: `AmazonShipping_UK`, `AmazonShipping_US`, `AmazonShipping_UAE`, `AmazonShipping_EG`, `AmazonShipping_IN`, `AmazonShipping_JP`, `AmazonShipping_IT`, `AmazonShipping_FR`, `AmazonShipping_ES`, `AmazonShipping_SA` > âš ï¸ Other optional variables (used in **(Optional)** requests like `cancelShipment` or `getTracking`) will be auto-generated when you run the flow. You can fill them in later if needed. --- ### ðŸ§ª Running the Flow 1. Head to the **Flows** tab 2. Select the **\[Shipping\] Buy Shipping Flow** flow 3. Enter required details: - `order_id` - Package info (weight, dimensions) - Label dimensions 4. Hit **Run** Youâ€™ll get: - A generated **Shipment ID** - A **Tracking ID** - The **Shipping Label**, ready to go > ðŸ’¡ Want to cancel the shipment? > Use the `cancelShipment` operation and make sure to copy the `shipmentId` from the flow results.

request.description:
Returns detailed order item information for the order that you specify. If NextToken is provided, it's used to retrieve the next page of order items.

__Note__: When an order is in the Pending state (the order has been placed but payment has not been authorized), the getOrderItems operation does not return information about pricing, taxes, shipping charges, gift status or promotions for the order items in the order. After an order leaves the Pending state (this occurs when payment has been authorized) and enters the Unshipped, Partially Shipped, or Shipped state, the getOrderItems operation returns information about pricing, taxes, shipping charges, gift status and promotions for the order items in the order.

request.description:
Purchases a shipping service and returns purchase related details and documents.

Note: You must complete the purchase within **10 minutes** of rate creation by the shipping service provider. If you make the request after the 10 minutes have expired, you will receive an error response with the error code equal to "TOKEN_EXPIRED". If you receive this error response, you must get the rates for the shipment again.
